        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 6:42PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Forest City. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forest City, Mayo, Chesnee, Cowpens National Battlefield, Cliffside,
Henrietta, Harris, and Caroleen.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
